bug.short_desc: Form leaves too little space for required field label

long_desc.thetext:
After upgrading to FireFox 4 I noticed that some required fields their labels are suddenly more than one line.
It is also visible in the demobrowser: http://demo.qooxdoo.org/current/demobrowser/#ui~FormRenderer.html

Hey, thanks for the report. Can't see anything strange on my mac here. Did you already check out the devel version? http://demo.qooxdoo.org/devel/demobrowser/#ui~FormRenderer.html This behavior sounds somehow familiar to me and it could be that we have already fixed it. Best, Martin
Just checked it out on linux and windows and cant see that behavior. Could you attach a screenshot and some more details about your setup?
Created attachment 928 FireFox4 Qooxdoo current demobrowser
Created attachment 929 FireFox4 Qooxdoo devel demobrowser

Just attached two screenshots, one of the current demobrowser and one of the devel demobrowser. As you can see the semicolons are being placed on a new line because the width of the column is too small.
We are using Windows Vista x64 systems here with FireFox 4.0 and using the latest stable Qooxdoo version 1.3 Everyone here is using the same system and is having the same issue. Don't know what else can be of interest for reproducing this bug, so if you need more info just let me know.
Thanks for the input. We currently have no vista system for testing here. But we will check that out as soon as we have the 1.4 release done.
I saw another bug report about the same problem, they fixed it with a patch: http://bugzilla.qooxdoo.org/show_bug.cgi?id=4961
That patch is already applied to the trunk (should be the same labels). Did you check if its still valid with the current trunk / devel version?

We just checke it on a System we could reproduce it and it is fixed with bug 4961.
*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of bug 4961 ***
Closed all bugs already shipped with a release.
